---
description: Mobile-first development rule for Chanda-Map
---

# Mobile-First Rule

> **This website primarily targets mobile users.** All design, development, and testing decisions must prioritize the mobile experience above desktop.

## Requirements

1. **Design mobile-first**: Always write CSS starting from the smallest screen, then use `min-width` media queries to add desktop enhancements.
2. **Test on mobile viewport first**: When verifying any change in the browser, always check at 375px width before checking desktop.
3. **Touch targets**: All buttons and interactive elements must be at least 44×44px for comfortable tapping.
4. **Font sizes**: Body text ≥ 14px, headings should scale down gracefully on small screens.
5. **No horizontal scroll**: Ensure no content overflows the viewport on mobile.
6. **Performance**: Keep assets lightweight — mobile users may be on slower connections.
7. **Navigation**: The mobile hamburger menu and all nav interactions must be smooth and intuitive.
8. **Map interactions**: The Leaflet map must be fully usable on touch devices with proper pinch-zoom and tap interactions.
